========================================================
1. TOP‑LEVEL NAVIGATION (5 SEPARATE ACTIVITIES)
========================================================

Your app consists of five independent screens, each with its
own .kt file and its own XML layout file:

1. Main UI / Chat
   - MainActivity.kt
   - activity_main.xml

2. Projects
   - ProjectsActivity.kt
   - activity_projects.xml

3. Settings
   - ProviderSettingsActivity.kt
   - activity_provider_settings.xml

4. API Keys
   - ApiKeysActivity.kt
   - activity_api_keys.xml

5. Security
   - SecurityActivity.kt
   - activity_security.xml

Why this structure:
- Clean separation of concerns
- Easy debugging
- Easy to remember which .kt matches which .xml
- Zero UI clutter
- Maximum scalability
- Perfect for full‑file regen workflow on mobile


========================================================
2. BACKEND ARCHITECTURE (PYTHON)
========================================================

Python backend files:

- backend.py
  Unified message router, timestamps, provider routing.

- providers.py
  OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Local provider logic.

- storage.py
  Loads config.json (unencrypted fallback).

- config_crypto.py
  Decrypts encrypted config.enc using seed phrase.

Android Activities call Python functions through Chaquopy.

Why this matters:
- Kotlin → XML → Python chain stays clean
- Encryption isolated from provider logic
- Debugging stays simple
- No spaghetti code


========================================================
3. SECURITY TAB STRUCTURE (SecurityActivity.kt)
========================================================

SecurityActivity contains three major sections inside a
single scrollable layout:

A) Seed Phrase Section (top)
   - Generate seed phrase
   - Display seed phrase
   - Save seed phrase
   - Validate seed phrase
   - Encrypt config.enc using seed phrase

B) Backup / Restore Section (middle)
   - Export encrypted config.enc
   - Import encrypted config.enc
   - Validate seed phrase before restore
   - Success/failure messages

C) Danger Zone (bottom, collapsible)
   - Reset encryption
   - Delete config.enc
   - Delete IV
   - Clear seed phrase flag
   - Confirmation dialogs
   - Hidden behind dropdown/collapse panel

Why this matters:
- Sensitive operations isolated
- Users cannot accidentally wipe config
- Backup/restore stays simple
- UI stays clean and professional


========================================================
4. API KEYS TAB STRUCTURE (ApiKeysActivity.kt)
========================================================

This screen is completely separate from Security:

- OpenAI key
- Anthropic key
- Gemini key
- Local provider settings
- Auto‑detect provider key
- Save buttons
- Model selectors
- Provider routing options

Why this matters:
- API keys stay away from Danger Zone
- Users don’t mix encryption with key entry
- Clean mental model
- Easy debugging
- Easy future expansion


========================================================
5. SETTINGS TAB STRUCTURE (ProviderSettingsActivity.kt)
========================================================

This screen handles general app settings:

- Default provider selection
- Model selection
- Routing preferences
- UI preferences
- Buttons to open:
  - Security tab
  - API Keys tab
  - Projects tab

Why this matters:
- Settings stay general
- Security stays isolated
- API keys stay isolated
- Navigation stays simple


